    {
      "id": "PopularPost75102",
      "post_content": "It's important to note that this is extended legal... unlike the common dismissals in preference to [counterspell](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=counterspell), [force of will](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=force of will), and the like. People seem to ignore the fact that it's the closest to a no-strings, unconditional counterspell you'll get for 2 mana in that format, disappointing that it's not standard though. Closest you'd get otherwise is [Delay](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Delay), and I'm sure we can all agree that [Remand](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Remand) is better than that in almost any case.  \n  \nImagine playing against a black deck, and [Remand](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Remand)ing something they need to play a [Dark Ritual](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dark Ritual) for. They've got another 2-3 turns to wait before they can replay the card, and you don't lose anything out of your hand for it. On turn two, you can send a spell back to their hand until turn 3, when you have enough for a hard-counter like [Farie Trickery](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Farie Trickery) or [Counter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Counter).  \n  \nIt's a matter of control-... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Zaneshift",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost75102\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl05_post\">It's important to note that this is extended legal... unlike the common dismissals in preference to <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=counterspell\">counterspell</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=force of will\">force of will</a>, and the like. People seem to ignore the fact that it's the closest to a no-strings, unconditional counterspell you'll get for 2 mana in that format, disappointing that it's not standard though. Closest you'd get otherwise is <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Delay\">Delay</a>, and I'm sure we can all agree that <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Remand\">Remand</a> is better than that in almost any case.<br/><br/>Imagine playing against a black deck, and <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Remand\">Remand</a>ing something they need to play a <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dark Ritual\">Dark Ritual</a> for. They've got another 2-3 turns to wait before they can replay the card, and you don't lose anything out of your hand for it. On turn two, you can send a spell back to their hand until turn 3, when you have enough for a hard-counter like <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Farie Trickery\">Farie Trickery</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Counter\">Counter</a>.<br/><br/>It's a matter of control-... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 75102)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl05_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=5