    {
      "id": "PopularPost135146",
      "post_content": "This isn't just an efficient hard counter/bounce with a cantrip. I can see this being used alongside cards like [Lobotomy](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lobotomy), [Thought Hemorrhage](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Thought Hemorrhage), and [Memoricide](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Memoricide) (Also Cranial Extraction.) I'm aware that [Counterbore](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Counterbore) combines both the functions of Cranial Extraction and any lay counter, but Counterbore is also mana intensive and there's just a point early to midgame where you can't sit around with 5 mana open for one spell.",
